The price of petrol is expected to increase by 43 cents per litre in March, said the AA. Commenting on unaudited mid-month fuel price data from the the Central Energy Fund, it said oil prices have increased steadily in February. “At the same time, the rand has been on a weakening trend against the US dollar since the start of February,” said the AA. Its predictions for fuel prices are: “If the trendlines for oil and the rand don’t flatten out, there could be worse to come before month end,” it concluded.